Key Match Events: Mike Yastrzemski hit a game-winning home run to take the lead in the seventh inning, securing the 5-4 win.
Pre-Game Insights: The San Francisco Giants needed a big win heading into the game against the Milwaukee Brewers.
Post-Match Reflections: San Francisco moved to 67-66 on the season and kept themselves alive in the chase to get back into a National League Wild Card spot.
Miscellaneous Highlights: San Francisco opened up the game with a 1-0 lead after Lamonte Wade Jr. grounded out to second, scoring Grant McCray. Matt Chapman also hit a solo home run in the top of the fourth and McCray added his own solo homer in the top of the fifth.
